[thinking] **Evaluating test focus**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering how generated tests could potentially focus on one format, like apt, to exercise Doxia parsing and rendering. It’s interesting to think if just one extra dependency would be sufficient. But then again, it seems that the library usually supports multiple formats through various modules. I’m wondering if this approach could simplify testing or if it might limit flexibility in the long run.
