 those methods. It's kind of tricky to keep all this straight!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating dependencies for testing**\\n\\nI'm considering that the artifact depends on `org.eclipse.sisu.plexus` for compilation but not on `plexus-testing`. To use the `PlexusTest` annotation, I need to include `plexus-testing`. I wonder if tests can instantiate `DefaultPlexusContainer` from transitive dependencies.\\n\\nMaybe the POM should include `plexus-component-annotations` and `plexus-classworlds`. Also, I should check if `PlexusContainer` API is transitive.\\n\\nI plan to include key dependencies like `maven-artifact` for context creation, `doxia-module-apt` for parsing, and consider test coverage options.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Maven dependencies**\\n\\nI'm considering the common Maven site src/site/apt and the POM comments related to \\\"doxia-module-apt/xdoc/fml test scope.\\\" I think including all modules that upstream tests use, like apt, xdoc, fml, might risk overadding dependencies, though those entries could be harmless. Still, more dependencies might complicate metadata generation. It seems like I need to focus on minimal requirements. I'll also look into documentation research for providing test-code setup guidance with environment variables.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Finalizing dependency decisions**\\n\\nI'm focused on how deterministic entries apply before generation and ensuring agent guidance doesn't restate dependencies. We need to prepare an output action, taking into account that deterministic setup isn't empty. I should summarize the risks while ensuring it stays valid JSON. \\n\\nI'm thinking about whether to include two dependencies and feeling more confident in my decisions. The `org.apache.maven:maven-artifact:3.6.3` might not be necessary unless I'm using `createContextForSkin`. The DefaultSiteRenderer now requires setting `context.getSkin()`, so meaningful coverage might make the maven-artifact necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_CP4w7Opv5ikhQBCYcAUPTVdT|fc_094bf12d7ed48f5b016a3f673187588193bd04ae3ef35747bb", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request,re\np=urllib.request.urlopen('https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/doxia/doxia-sitetools/2.0.0/doxia-sitetools-2.0.0.pom',timeout=20).read().decode()\nfor a in ['plexus-testing','org.eclipse.sisu.plexus','javax.inject']:\n i=p.find(f'<artifactId>{a}</artifactId>')\n print('\\n',a, i)\n print(p[i-200:i+300] if i!=-1 else '')\nPY", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 673, "output": 1904, "cacheRead": 35328, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37905, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782540041002, "responseId": "resp_094bf12d7ed48f5b016a3f6709a06c819389a2666066039186"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_CP4w7Opv5ikhQBCYcAUPTVdT|fc_094bf12d7ed48f5b016a3f673187588193bd04ae3ef35747bb", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\n plexus-testing 6616\n        <artifactId>guice</artifactId>\r\n        <version>6.0.0</version>\r\n        <scope>test</scope>\r\n      </dependency>\r\n      <dependency>\r\n        <groupId>org.codehaus.plexus</groupId>\r\n        <artifactId>plexus-testing</artifactId>\r\n        <version>1.4.0</version>\r\n        <scope>test</scope>\r\n      </dependency>\r\n    </dependencies>\r\n  </dependencyManagement>\r\n\r\n  <build>\r\n    <resources>\r\n      <resource>\r\n        <directory>src/main/resources</directory>\r\n      </resource>\r\n      <re\n\n org.eclipse.sisu.plexus -1\n\n\n javax.inject 6024\n      <artifactId>slf4j-simple</artifactId>\r\n        <version>${slf4jVersion}</version>\r\n      </dependency>\r\n      <!-- misc -->\r\n      <dependency>\r\n        <groupId>javax.inject</groupId>\r\n        <art